NAME: Lowdermilk Park
NOTES: Lowdermilk Park is a developed beach in the City of Naples. Access to 900 feet of beach frontage is at Bayan Boulevard, west off Gulf Shores Boulevard North.

NAME: Tigertail Beach Park
NOTES: Access through residential area. Beach on tidal lagoon, over looking a barrier island.

NAME: South Marco Beach Access
NOTES: South Marco Beach, on Southwest Marco Island, is accessible from Collier Boulevard. Foot shower only. Parking, restroom & additional foot shower located across street.

NAME: Perdido Key State Park - East Use Area
NOTES: Closed due to hurricane damage at the time of this survey.

NAME: Big Lagoon State Park - West Beach
Gulf Islands National Seashore - Perdido Key Area - Rosamond Johnson Beach
NOTES: Trails closed due to hurricane damage.

NAME: Gulf Islands National Seashore - Fort Pickens & Langdon Beach
NOTES: Area has suffered severe hurricane damage. Road to Langdon Beach.

NAME: Pensacola Beach (2)
NOTES: Four parking areas along SR 399. Handicap parking.

NAME: Quietwater Beach
NOTES: Handicap parking.

NAME: Big Lagoon State Park - East Beach & Tower
NOTES: Observation tower.

NAME: Casino Beach
NOTES: Handicap parking & restrooms.

NAME: Pensacola Beach (1)
NOTES: Beach Access at Avenida 10, 15, 16, 17, 18 & 23. Extreme hurricane damage.

NAME: Perdido Key State Park - West Use Area
NOTES: Closed due to hurricane damage at the time of this survey.

NAME: Gulf Islands National Seashore/Santa Rosa Recreational Facility
NOTES: Gulf Islands National Seashore/Santa Rosa Recreational Facility. 106 acres of developed recreation beach on both Santa Rosa Sound and the Gulf of Mexico, located 10 miles east of Pensacola Beach on SR 399.
NOTES_2: Closed due to hurricane damage.

NAME: Navarre Beach
NOTES: Navarre Beach Access is at Gulf Blvd. & SR 399. Pedestrian access down Gulf Blvd. at Sonata Ct. Handicap parking & beach access. Facilities limited due to severe hurricane damage.

NAME: Navarre Beach State Park
NOTES: Closed due to hurricane damage.

NAME: Shoreline Park
NOTES: Shoreline Park, a small, community recreation area on Santa Rosa Sound, lies on both sides of the Navarre Beach Bridge.

NAME: Destin Beach Access - East
NOTES:
Destin Beach Access (roadside parking & small parking lots):
Pompano St. (parking)
Barracuda St.
Crystal Beach Dr.
Hutchinson St. (parking, shower)
Shirah St. (parking)

NAME: Garniers Beach Park
NOTES: Handicap parking, restrooms & beach access.

NAME: Blue Dolphin Beachwalk
NOTES: Okaloosa Beach Access #1. Handicap parking, restrooms & beach access (closed due to hurricane damage). Lifeguards on duty Sautrday & Sunday, 9AM-5PM.

NAME: June Decker Park
NOTES: June Decker Park, located off US 98, is still under construction.

NAME: Newman C. Brackin Wayside Park & Fishing Pier (The Boardwalk)
NOTES: Newman C. Brackin Wayside Park & Fishing Pier is accessed from US 98.

NAME: John C. Beasley Park
NOTES: Lifeguards on beach Saturday & Sunday, 9AM-5PM. Handicap parking, restrooms & beach access (closed due to hurricane damage).

NAME: Gulf Islands National Seashore/Okaloosa Area
NOTES: Gulf Islands National Seashore/Okaloosa Area (formerly Fort Walton Beach Park), located on Santa Rosa Island east of Fort Walton Beach on US 98. Small craft launch to Choctawhatchee Bay.
NOTES_2: Closed due to hurricane damage.

NAME: Henderson Beach State Park
NOTES: Henderson Beach State Park is accessed from US 98, just east of Destin.

NAME: James Lee Park
NOTES: James Lee Park is located on US 98, just west of the Okaloosa-Walton County Line. Facilities are under construction due to major hurricane damage.

NAME: Miramar Beach
NOTES: Due to severe hurricane damage, Miramar Beach Park, next to Pompano Joe's, is closed. Beach still accessible at other points down Old Hwy 98.

NAME: Grayton Beach
NOTES: Access at the end of Garfield St. Handicap parking & walkway. Other facilites under construction at the time of this survey.

NAME: Camp Helen State Park
NOTES: Camp Helen State Park is located at the Walton-Bay County Line, on US 98.

NAME: Dune Allen Beach
NOTES: Dune Allen Beach is west of the intersection of SR 393 and 30A. Very limited parking at Oyster Lake Cswy and pedestrian access at Allen Loop Dr.

NAME: Blue Mountain Beach
NOTES: Blue Mountain Beach located off SR 30A. Currently under going beach refurbishment. Parking & access at CR 83. Limited parking and access at Sea Grade Rd (closed). Pedestrian access at Blue Lake Rd. & Gulf Point Rd. (closed).

NAME: Grayton Beach State Park
NOTES: Grayton Beach State Park is 356 acres of pine woodlands, freshwater lakes, and white beaches situated between Western Lake and the Gulf of Mexico and reached at the southern end of SR 283 on SR 30A. Beverage vending machines.

NAME: Seagrove Beach
NOTES: Seagrove Beach is 1.5 miles fronting the Gulf, reached by turning east from SR 395 onto SR 30A to a point near Deer Lake. This beach was undergoing refurbishment at the time of this survey. Very limited roadside parking.

NAME: Inlet Beach
NOTES: Located on W. Park Place Ave., at N. Orange St. Additional parking along Emerald Cove Ln.

NAME: Panama City Beach
NOTES: Panama City Beach has about 1,400 feet of developed, urban beach facing the Gulf of Mexico. Walkways and street-end easements to the 9 miles of beach maintained within the corporate city limits.

NAME: Panama City Beach Pier
NOTES: On Front Beach Rd., between Alf Coleman Rd. & Lyndell Ln.

NAME: St. Andrews State Park
NOTES: St. Andrews State Park is located at the east end of SR 392 in Panama City Beach. This 1,063-acre developed park also includes a primitive area on the western third of Shell Island, accessible only by boat.

NAME: Mexico Beach & Pier
NOTES: Mexico Beach reaches 3 miles west from the Gulf County Line. Access at 1st, 3rd to 6th, 9th, 11th and 15th Streets, 23rd St. to Canal Parkway. Public Pier located at 36th Street. Restrooms, showers and parking at some access points.

NAME: Beacon Hill
NOTES: Beacon Hill lies 0.7 miles from the Bay County line on US 98. Access at Abalone, Helmet & Triton Streets. Roadside parking.

NAME: St. Joe Beach
NOTES: This north county coastal area is open beach without facilities. Parking is along SR 30 (US 98). Access at Pine, Selma, Pineda, Columbus and Court Streets and between Gulf Aire Dr. & Beacon Rd.

NAME: Indian Pass
NOTES: Indian Pass is located at the eastern end of the Miracle Strip beaches on Indian Peninsula. Situated between St. Vincent's Island and St. Joseph Peninsula State Park, this area is the natural opening from Apalachicola Bay to the Gulf of Mexico.
NOTES_2: Access at the east end of Indian Pass Rd. and S. Oak St. Concessions available at adjacent campground store.

NAME: Cape San Blas
NOTES: Cape San Blas is located on the south end of St. Joseph Spit about 14 miles from Port St. Joe. Named for the lighthouse first built in 1847, the existing loran station (long-range aid to navigation) serves as a modern aid to boating.
NOTES_2: No facilities due to severe hurricane damage.

NAME: North Redington Beach Access
NOTES: There is limited street parking along Gulf Blvd. (SR699) and 3 hour public parking at Bath Club Concourse.  There are four access points between 173rd and 170th Avenues and one at Bath Club Circle.
NOTES_2: Shelter and shower are located at the North Redington Beach Gulf Front Park at 169th Ave.

NAME: Redington Beach
NOTES: Redington Beach has boardwalk access at 163rd, 158th and 155th Avenues.  Shower is located at the Redington Beach Xeriscape Garden and Gulf Access at 160th Ave.  No public parking available.

NAME: Archibald Memorial Beach Park
NOTES: Archibald Memorial Beach has 5.5 acres of developed recreation area on the Gulf. Group facilities. Marked access is off SR 699 about 0.2 miles north of Welch Causeway.
NOTES_2: The building housing consessions and other aminities is currently closed and under construction.

NAME: Madeira Beach Access
NOTES: Madeira Beach Access is 1.5 miles of undeveloped beachfront on Gulf Boulevard in Madeira Beach (SR 699) at 148th Street, 142nd Street, 141st Street, and 137th Street through 129th Street.

NAME: Tom & Kitty Stuart County Park
NOTES: Madeira Beach County Park is a half mile south of Welch Causeway on SR 699. This park has 300 feet of developed beach frontage.

NAME: Johns Pass Beach & Park
NOTES: Johns Pass Beach and Park lies 1.5 miles south of Madeira Beach on SR 699. It is developed with dune walkovers to 500 feet of beachfront and a fishing pier. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Treasure Island Beach Access
NOTES: Treasure Island Beach Access lies north of St. Petersburg Beach on SR 699. There are 45 dune walkovers and street ends giving access to the gulfside beach between 77th Avenue and 127th Avenue and 20 street ends provide bayside beach access.
NOTES_2: Three (123rd Ave, 100th Ave, and 94th Ave) have boat ramps. Night access prohibited (1-5 AM).

NAME: St. Petersburg Municipal Beach at Treasure Island
NOTES: Treasure Island Beach has 0.7 miles on the Gulf of Mexico developed for recreation. There is access along Gulf Boulevard (SR 699) in Treasure Island.  While there is handicapped parking and access to the beach, there are no handicap-accessable restrooms.

NAME: Upham Beach
NOTES: Upham Beach is 9 acres of developed beach on Long Key. Across the channel lies Treasure Island Park. However, access is through St. Petersburg Beach SR A19A to 71st Avenue West. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: St. Pete Beach Access
NOTES: St. Petersburg Municipal Beach is developed with street access from 80th Street to 24th Street off Gulf Boulevard and SR A19A.

NAME: Pass-a-Grille Beach
NOTES: Pass-a-Grille Beach Park has 5,200 feet of gulffront with unlimited access.

NAME: Fort DeSoto County Park East Beach
NOTES: East Beach is the beach access point nearest the entrance to Ft. De Soto Park. Park Headquarters is located nearby as well. A multi-purpose trail, most of which is barrier-free, winds around the island,
NOTES_2: taking you near the historic Fort and other excellent sights. Access is via the Pinellas Bayway (SR679). This is a well-developed recreation area, as well as a bird, plant and animal sanctuary.

NAME: Anna Maria Beach
NOTES: Anna Maria Beach, on the north point of Anna Maria Island, has 3 acres of undeveloped beach with access from private residential street ends facing the Gulf. There are a few pedestrian access points to the beach along North Shore Drive,
NOTES_2: from the bayside around to the gulfside, and then at most streets from Spruce Ave. to Park Ave. Access ramps available at Sycamore, Elm, Spring, Palmetto and Oak Avenues.

NAME: Anna Maria Bayfront Park
NOTES: Bayfront Park has 1,000 feet of beach along Tampa Bay. Located in the city of Anna Maria, this developed park with 150 parking places can be reached off Bay Boulevard.
NOTES_2: Access to the Historic Anna Maria City Pier. Restrooms and concessions located here. Fishing allowed off pier.

NAME: Holmes Beach
NOTES: Holmes Beach runs 14,400 feet along the Gulf of Mexico. It is reached off Gulf Drive (SR 789) from Beach Avenue to 27th Street.  There is limited parking available at 77th, 68th, 65th, 52nd, 50th, 46th, 45th, 36th, 33rd, 31st, 30th and 28th Streets.
NOTES_2: The beach is currently undergoing refurbishment.

NAME: Manatee County Beach
NOTES: Manatee County Beach has 900 feet of developed beach fronting the Gulf of Mexico. Marked access is at 4000 Gulf Dr (SR789).

NAME: Palma Sola Causeway
NOTES: Palma Sola Causeway, the Manatee Avenue (SR 64) crossing of Palma Sola Bay, has access to 3,000 feet of developed beach on both sides and at each end of the causeway.  The Causeway beach is currently undergoing restoration and beautification efforts.

NAME: Cortez Beach
NOTES: Cortez Beach has 140 feet of undeveloped beach reached off Gulf Drive (SR 789) between 5th and 13th Streets, fronting the Gulf of Mexico in Bradenton Beach.  Handicapped parking & access ramp are located at 10th St.

NAME: Coquina Beach
NOTES: Coquina Beach has over 5,000 feet of developed beach on the Gulf of Mexico with a boat ramp to Sarasota Bay. Access is off Gulf Dr (SR 789) at the southern end of Anna Maria Island, about one mile south of SR 684 (5th St N) in the City of Bradenton Beach
NOTES_2: A catamaran launch site and fishing groin are off to the right before the bridge over Longboat Pass is crossed. Shelters and group facilities are located at the south end of the beach.

NAME: Beer Can Island
NOTES: Beer Can Island has 2,000 feet of undeveloped beach on the northern end of Longboat Key. Access to the hooked-spit beach is by walking north on the beach from the North Shore access point off the Gulf of Mexico Drive.
NOTES_2: This access point was closed at the time of this survey.

NAME: Longboat Key Beach Access - North
NOTES: Longboat Key Beach Access extends along the barrier island south from North Shore Road to the county line.  Access to the northern part of the beach is available at North Shore (closed at the time of survey), Seabreeze and Broadway; parking at Broadway.

NAME: Longboat Key Beach Access
NOTES: Longboat Key Beaches are 3.75 miles northwest of Lido Key along SR 789 (Gulf of Mexico Drive).  There are 3 access points, with limited parking, within the 3000 block of Gulf of Mexico Dr (north of Buttonwood Dr) and at Neptune Ave.
NOTES_2: Beach restoration is currently in progress.

NAME: North Lido Beach Park
NOTES: Main entrance to North Lido Beach Park is at Emerson Dr; access to the beach is also available at Whitter and Bryant Drives.

NAME: Lido Beach Park
NOTES: Lido Beach is 3,000 feet long; it has lifeguards 9AM to 5PM and a 25-meter pool and is developed.

NAME: South Lido Park
NOTES: South Lido Park has both gulf and bay access; swimming is allowed only on the bayside.

NAME: Siesta Key Beach - North
NOTES: Access to the northern part of Siesta Key Beach is at Shell Rd; parking along this residential street is very limited and the beach is not well marked.

NAME: Siesta Key Beach Park
NOTES: Siesta Key Beach Park, almost 1/2 mile long, is developed and has lifeguards. It is along the south side of Beach Road, west of the Midnight Pass Road intersection.

NAME: Turtle Beach
NOTES: Boat ramp is located at Little Sarasota Bay.  Restroom facilities are currently under construction (port-a-potties available).

NAME: Palmer Point Beach
NOTES: Palmer Point Beach begins at the southern tip of Siesta Key and continues onto the north end of Casey Key.  Access by walking south along Turtle Beach.

NAME: Nokomis Beach
NOTES: Nokomis Beach is a developed, lifeguarded beach 0.2 miles long. It includes beaches on the Gulf and is one mile west of the Tamiami Trail (US 41) on SR 789 at the intersection of Casey Key Road.

NAME: North Jetty Park
NOTES: North Jetty Park, almost 0.2 miles long, is developed and has lifeguards. It also fronts both the Gulf and bay and is 0.6 miles south of SR 789 on Casey Key Road, at the sound end of the key. One of the Gulf's best surfing beaches.

NAME: Venice Municipal Beach
NOTES: Venice Municipal Beach, 600 feet long, is developed and has lifeguards. It is 0.9 miles west of US 41 on Venice Avenue West at Gulf.

NAME: Brohard Park - Service Club Park
NOTES: Vending machines available.  Beach is currently undergoing restoration efforts.

NAME: Manasota Beach
NOTES: Manasota Beach, a quarter mile long, is developed and has lifeguards year-round. It is on Manasota Key at the west end of Manasota Bridge.  Boat ramp and scenic boardwalk located across Manasota Key Road.

NAME: Blind Pass Park
NOTES: Blind Pass Beach, 2,000 feet long, is undeveloped. It is 3.6 miles south of Manasota Bridge and fronts both Lemon Bay and the Gulf.  Vending machine available.  Picnic and play area located across Manasota Key Road.

NAME: Englewood Beach at Chadwick Park
NOTES: Englewood Beach is developed with 600 feet of coastline, situated between Lemon Bay and the Gulf of Mexico on Manasota Key. Access is via SR 776 from the mainland. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Stump Pass Beach State Park
NOTES: Port Charlotte Beach Park has 25 acres south of Englewood Beach at the southern end of Manasota Key. The only access to this undeveloped beach is SR 776.  Watercraft access from Lemon Bay.

NAME: Don Pedro Island Complex
NOTES: Don Pedro Island complex is an undeveloped beach on the barrier island that can be reached only by boat.

NAME: Boca Grande
NOTES: Boca Grande accessways are located on Gasparilla Island, a barrier island between the Gulf of Mexico and Charlotte Harbor. Access to residential area beach is off the west side of Gulf Blvd (SR 771 S) street ends: 19th, 17th, 14th, 13th and 10th.
NOTES_2: Public parking is available at these west side streets: 17th, 14th-9th, 5th-3rd, Banyan & 1st St; and these east side streets: 19th, 17th, 15th, 13th and 9th. Fishing pier access at 15th St. A multi-purpose path runs down most of the island to Belcher Rd

NAME: Gasparilla Island State Park - Sand Spur Beach
NOTES: Sand Spur Beach is the first beach access point with Gasparilla Island State Park.

NAME: Gasparilla Island State Park - Lighthouse Beach
NOTES: Lighthouse Beach Park occupies the southern end of Gasparilla Island and has 400 feet of undeveloped beach. Access is at the southern street end of Gulf Boulevard (SR 771). Fishing pier.  There is no swimming allowed in this area.

NAME: Cayo Costa Island Park
NOTES: Cayo Costa Island Park has 625 acres of isolated and undeveloped beach between the Gulf of Mexico and Pine Island Sound. The only access is by boat. Alcohol is not permitted.

NAME: Captiva Beach Access
NOTES: Main Captiva Beach Access point, at the north end of Captiva Dr, is closed for construction.  Other access points, at Ande Rossi Ln & Wightman Ln, do not have parking.

NAME: Turner Beach
NOTES: Turner Beach has 3 acres of developed beach at the south end of Captiva Island. Access is off SR 867. Parking on both sides on Causeway.

NAME: Bowman's Beach Park
NOTES: Bowman's Beach is an emerged sandbar on the north end of Sanibel Island. Marked access is from SR 867. Fitness trail. Beverage vending machine available.

NAME: Gulfside City Park at Algiers Beach
NOTES: Gulfside City Park/Algiers Beach is a developed beach with 30 acres on the Gulf of Mexico in Ybel. Access is at the beach end of Algiers Ln.

NAME: Flowing Well
NOTES: Flowing Well has access to more than a half mile of beach at Beach Rd, Nerita, Donax and Falgur Streets. Ramps at Nerita and Donax closed.

NAME: Sanibel - Gulf
NOTES: Access at Buttonwood and Seagrape Lanes, and at E Gulf Dr & Bella Vista Way.

NAME: Lighthouse Beach Park - Main Beach
NOTES: Lighthouse Park is 5 acres of undeveloped beach at Point Ybel. Access is at the end of Periwinkle Way in Sanibel.

NAME: Sanibel - Bay
NOTES: Access at Buttonwood and Seagrape Lanes.

NAME: Fort Myers Beach County Access (1)
NOTES:
Beach access points #37-41 along Estero Blvd; no parking available.
Beach access points #23-36:
No parking:
Canal St, Avenues A & C, Alva Dr, Avenue E, Miramar Dr, Chapel St, Gulf Beach Rd.
NOTES_2:
Beach access points #23-36 (con't):
Very limited parking:
Delmar Ave
Mango, Pompano & Seaview Streets

Limited parking:
Palm Ave.

NAME: Bunche Beach
NOTES: Bunche Beach is a mainland beach on San Carlos Bay across from Fort Myers Beach (Estero Island). Access is SR 867 west from Fort Myers south to John Morris Road.

NAME: Lovers Key State Park - Black Island
NOTES: Kayak/canoe rentals & launch. Black Island Trail. Public transportation to park; trams available within park.

NAME: Bonita Beach County Access
NOTES: County beach access #2-9. Very limited parking available at all access points.

NAME: Delnor Wiggins State Park
NOTES:
Five Gulf-side parking areas available. All facilities available at each area except as noted.
Parking area #5:
Concessesions available only at this area.
Observation tower.
Swimming & fishing restricted here.

NAME: Clam Pass County Park
NOTES: Access via tram or along mangrove boardwalk. Canoe/kayak trail.

NAME: Gulf Shore Beach Access
NOTES: Parking off of Bluebill Ave.

NAME: Ft. Lauderdale Beach
NOTES: Fort Lauderdale Beach has access to over 21,000 feet of devleoped crushed shell/coarse sand beach. Access street ends: Oakland Park Blvd. (SR 816), NE 30th St., Vista Park, NE 27th St., NE 25th St., NE 23rd St., NE 22nd St., NE 21st St.,
NOTES_2: North Atlantic 1900 block, and Sunrise Blvd (US 1). Additional open access may be had alon SR A1A where it parallels the beach. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Hugh Taylor Birch State Park
NOTES: Hugh Taylor Birch State Park has access to 400 feet of beach. It is a developed state recreation area that extends from the Atlantic Ocean to the Intracoastal Waterway.
NOTES_2: Access from Fort Lauderdale is east on Sunrise Blvd (US 1) to North Atlantic Blvd (SR A1A). No alcohol allowed.

NAME: John U. Lloyd State Recreation Area
NOTES: John U. Lloyed State Recreation Area covers 244 acres of barrier island north of Dania. Access is on Dania Beach Blvd (SR A1A). This developed state recreation area has over 11,000 feet of beach frontage with lifeguarded areas. No alcohol permitted.

NAME: Dania Beach
NOTES: Dania Beach has 1,000 feet of undeveloped beach. Access is east off SR A1A on Oak St.

NAME: Hollywood Beach
NOTES: Hollywood Beach has over 5 miles of developed beach with lifeguards. Street-end access off North Ocean Dr. No alcohol is allowed. There is a catamaran launch and community center.
NOTES_2: Hollywood Boardwalk is a wide sidewalk area bordered to the east by beach and the west by rows of shops, restaurants, and hotels.

NAME: Hallandale Beach
NOTES: Hallandale Beach is a developed beach with five dune walkways off Ocean Blvd., south of SR 824. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Golden Beach
NOTES: Golden Beach, 1.5 miles of undeveloped beach, is difficult to enter. There is a parking lot at 196th St. and a dune walkover at 195th St.; both are on Ocean Blvd. (SR A1A). No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Loggia Beach
NOTES: Loggia Beach lies off SR A1A in Golden Beach. Access to this undeveloped beach is on Ocean Blvd. opposite the entrance to Central Island. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Sunny Isles Beach and Pier
NOTES: Sunny Isles Beach and Pier lies on the barrier island off North Miami Beach. Access to this developed recreation area is at the intersection of Sunny Isles Causeway (SR 826) and Collins Ave. (SR A1A).

NAME: Haulover Beach and Pier
NOTES: Haulover Beach and Pier has 172 acres of developed beach with lifeguards. Access is one-half mile south of SR 826 (Sunny Isles Rd.) on Collins Ave. (SR A1A). No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Bal Harbour/Surfside
NOTES: Bal Harbour/Surfside have 2 miles of undeveloped beach. Public access along Collins Ave (SR A1A) at 96th , 95,th, 92nd, 90th, 89th, and 88th streets.

NAME: North Shore Ocean Front Park
NOTES: North Shore Ocean Front Park has 24 acres of developed beach with lifeguards. Access and parking are available east on 79th St. Additional parking is between 84th/85th St. and 81st/80th St., west off Collins Ave. (SR A1A). No alcohol allowed.

NAME: North Shore Park
NOTES: North Shore Park lies on the barrier island between Biscayne Bay and the Atlantic Ocean. It has 36 acres of developed beach with lifeguard areas. Access points along Collins Ave. at 77th St., 74th St., 73rd St., 71st St. (SR 828), and 69th St.
NOTES_2: Parking lots are off Collins Ave. at 76th/75th St., Ocean Terrace, and 73rd/ 72nd St.

NAME: 65th Street Park
NOTES: 65th Street Park, off Collins Ave, about 100 yards south of 65th St., has a small (1.5) acres), undeveloped, oceanfront beach with lifeguards.

NAME: Ocean Front Park
NOTES: Ocean Front Park lies on the barrier island between Indian Creek and the Atlantic Ocean. It is developed beach with lifeguards. Access is from Collins Ave., about 2 miles south of 71st St. (SR 828).

NAME: Indian Beach Park
NOTES: Indian Beach Park is on Collins Ave. about one-half mile north of Arthur Godfrey Rd. The park is the main access to almost 2 miles of boardwalk and beach with lifeguard areas.

NAME: Miami Beach
NOTES: Miami Beach provides public access to undeveloped beach east of Collins Ave. at street ends from 43rd St. through 29th St.

NAME: Collins Park
NOTES: Collins Park is a developed beach with lifeguards and access to the boardwalk. The park is situated between 21st St. and 22nd St.

NAME: Lummus Park
NOTES: Lummus Park has 48 acres of developed beachfront park with lifeguards. It is between 5th St. and 14th St. on Ocean Dr. in Miami Beach.

NAME: Ocean Beach
NOTES: Ocean Beach on Miami Beach is an undeveloped recreation area with lifeguards. This area of 6 acres is accessible at 2nd St. and 3rd St. on Ocean Dr., south of Lummus Park.

NAME: Pier Park
NOTES: Pier Park is at the intersection of Biscayne St. and Ocean Dr. at the south end of Miami Beach. This developed beach has more than 4 acres aof beach with lifeguards.

NAME: Government Cut Park
NOTES: Government Cut Park (South Point Park) at the southern tip of Miami Beach is under development and will be partly open in summer 1985.

NAME: Matheson Hammock County Park
NOTES: Matheson Hammock County Park has 580 acres of park and bay beach. Access to this developed park is off Old Cutler Rd. at 97th St. and Bay St. in South Coral Gables.

NAME: Virginia Beach
NOTES: Virginia Beach has 145 acres on Virginia Key between the mainland and Key Biscayne. Access is off Rickenbacker Causeway. Park is still in the planning-construction phase in 1985.

NAME: Crandon Park
NOTES: Crandon Park has 698 acres of developed ocean beach, north of Key Biscayne, on Crandon Blvd. Golf course is located within park.

NAME: Bill Baggs/Cape Florida State Recreation Area
NOTES: Bill Baggs/Cape Florida State Recreation Area lies at the south end of Key Biscayne. The 406-acre park is accessible off Crandon Blvd. No alcohol is allowed.

NAME: Everglades National Park
NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. The following are located off Monroe County's Gulf Coast.
NOTES_2: They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat. Major use is by overnight campers.

NAME: Indian Key
NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. The following are located off Monroe County's Gulf Coast.
NOTES_2: They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat. Major use is by overnight campers.

NAME: Turkey Key
NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. The following are located off Monroe County's Gulf Coast.
NOTES_2: They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat. Major use is by overnight campers.

NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. The following are located off Monroe County's Gulf Coast.
NOTES_2: They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat. Major use is by overnight campers.

NAME: Graveyard Creek
NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. The following are located off Monroe County's Gulf Coast.
NOTES_2: They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat. Major use is by overnight campers.

NAME: Northwest Cape
NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. The following are located off Monroe County's Gulf Coast.
NOTES_2: They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat. Major use is by overnight campers.

NAME: North Sand Key (Carl Ross Key)
NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. The following are located off Monroe County's Gulf Coast.
NOTES_2: They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat. Major use is by overnight campers.

NAME: Rabbit Key
NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. The following are located off Monroe County's Gulf Coast.
NOTES_2: They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat. Major use is by overnight campers.

NAME: Flamingo Visitor's Center
NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat.
NOTES_2: Major use is by overnight campers. Flamingo Visitor's Center is located at the southern end of the 100-mile Wilderness Waterway through the park's expanse of marsh area to the shallow waters of Florida Bay.

NAME: John Pennekamp Coral Reef State Park
NOTES: John Pennekamp Coral Reef State Park has 178 nautical square miles of coral reefs, seagrass beds, mangrove swamps, and a 2,640-foot land base with recreational facilities.
NOTES_2: This underwater state park fronts the Atlantic Ocean on Key Largo, south of Miami on US 1.

NAME: T.H. Stone Memorial St. Joseph Peninsula State Park - Gulf
NOTES: St. Joseph Peninsula State Park/T.H. Stone Memorial at the north end of SR 30E has 20 miles of white-sand beaches, freshwater ponds, and salt marshes. The park is surrounded by water and is characterized by striking dune formations.

NAME: St. Vincent Memorial Wildlife Refuge
NOTES: St. Vincent National Wildlife Refuge is located on an unusual triangular-shaped barrier island, 9 miles long, 4 miles wide on the east end, and gradually narrowing to a point on the west end of Indian Pass.
NOTES_2: All travel to the island is over water; no public transportation is available. Boat launch sites are located at Apalachicola on US 98 (SR C30). There are 14 miles of beaches along the south and east shores and 80 miles of inland trails.

NAME: St. George Island
NOTES: St. George Island is located near Apalachicola and across the bay from East Point. It is bordered by the Gulf on the south and Apalachicola Bay to the north and is linked to the mainland by a 4-mile causeway, off US 98. Play area.

NAME: Dr. Julian G. Bruce St. George Island State Park - East Slough Beach
NOTES: St. George Island State Park occupies 1,883 acres at the eastern end of the long, narrow St. George Island. Park closed past this point due to severe hurricane damage; Sugar Hill Camping & Beach Access Areas inaccessible.
NOTES_2: Boating facilites located just past park entrance.

NAME: Carrabelle Beach
NOTES: Carrabelle Beach, located one mile west of Carrabelle on US 98/319, has a gradual sloping beach on St. George Sound.

NAME: Dog Island
NOTES: Dog Island has isolated white-sand beaches just off the coast of Carrabelle.

NAME: Fort Clinch State Park - Atlantic
NOTES:
Hiking & biking trails run through the park.
Fishing pier at north end of beach.
Beverage vending machine.

NOTES_2: There are 4 trails through the park: Mala Compra Hiking Trail (.5 mi) and the Bella Vista Trail System - Jungle Road Hike & Bike Trail (.65 mi), Old A1A Hike & Bike Trail (.5 mi), and Timucuan Hiking Trail (.95 mi).

NAME: Flagler Beach
NOTES: Pedestrian access at 25th, 23rd-21st St S, 19th St S-23rd St N. Access at 18th S, 14th S, 12th S and 21st N is closed. There is road-side parking along most of the beach. The boardwalk, with parking & access to the pier, runs from 7th St S to Moody Blvd.

NOTES: Joe Kenner Nature Trail, boating & group facilities located across A1A.

NAME: Bethune Beach
NOTES: Bethune Beach has pedestrian access at Trout - Pompano Avenues, Kingfish - Dolphin Avenues and at Bullhead and Bass Avenues, all off S Atlantic Ave.

NAME: Canaveral National Seashore - Apollo Beach
NOTES: Canaveral National Seashore-Apollo Beach has 5 beach parking areas, 4 additional parking areas, with access to the Mosquito Lagoon, and multiple trails.
NOTES_2:
Area 1: Turtle Mound, 1/4-mile boardwalk-trail leading to the top of a Timucuan Indian Mound
Area 3: Castel Windy, 1-mile round trip trail that crosses the island from the beach to the Lagoon
Area 5: Boat launch
Area 7: Fishing dock & canoe launch
NOTES_3:
Area 8: Eldora, 1/4-mile trail leading to a turn-of-the century settlement along Mosquito Lagoon
Area 9: Eldora Hammock, 1/2-mile loop trail through the coastal forest

NAME: Canaveral National Seashore - Klondike Beach
NOTES: Canaveral National Seashore - Klondike Beach has 16 miles of remote, undeveloped oceanfront. This section of beach between Apollo and Playalind, at the Volusia-Brevard county line, is accessible by foot only.

NAME: Canaveral National Seashore - Playalinda Beach
NOTES: Canaveral National Seashore - Playalinda Beach is on the seashore's southern edge within easy viewing distance of the NASA rocket installations and may be closed at times of Kennedy Space Center activities. Access is west on SR 402 from Titusville.
NOTES_2: There are 13 parking areas, each with beach access and handicap accessable restrooms.  Boat launch is at Eddy Creek.

NAME: Jetty Park
NOTES: Fishing permitted off the Malcom McLouth Fishing Pier.  A multi-purpose trail runs through the park. Consessions available at the Jetty Park Camp Store.

NAME: Alan Shepard Park
NOTES: Guards are seasonal.

NAME: Sidney Fisher Park
NOTES: Guards are seasonal. Play area. Beverage vending machine.

NAME: Lori Wilson Park
NOTES: Johnnie Johnson Nature Center. Hammock Trail. Guards are seasonal. Play area. Beverage vending machine.

NAME: Cherie Down Park
NOTES: Guards are seasonal. Beverage vending machine.

NAME: Pelican Beach Park
NOTES: Pelican Beach Park is located 2.5 miles north of the intersection of SR 518 (Royal Palm Blvd) and SR A1A. Group facilities include a pavillion and a clubhouse.

NAME: Richard G. Edgeton Bicentennial Park - Indian Harbor Beach
NOTES: Bicentennial Park/Indian Harbor Beach has one acre of developed beach at the end of Ocean Dunes Drive in Indian Harbor Beach.

NAME: Howard E. Futch Memorial Park at Paradise Beach
NOTES: Guards are seasonal.

NAME: Long Point Park
NOTES: Long Point Park lies 2 miles northwest of the south county line on the west side of the barrier island. Beverage vending machines.

NAME: Sebastian Inlet State Park - North Entrance
NOTES: Sebastian Inlet State Recreation Area has 4,000 feet of beachfront and extends across the barrier island from the ocean to the Indian River. There is a bike trail and a hammock trail.

NAME: Sebastian Inlet State Park - Boardwalk
NOTES: The Boardwalk, several other small access points (with very limited parking) and the McLarty Treasure Museum are located south of the main entrance, along SR A1A.

NAME: Riverside Park
NOTES: Riverfront Park is located riverside of Vero Beach.  Concessions are located in the Tennis Club Pro Shop.  Fitness trail.  Pedestrian access to Veterans Memorial Island Park.

NAME: MacWilliams Park
NOTES: McWilliams Park is a riverside recreation area. Boating factilites are on the north side of Beachland Blvd; restrooms, handicap facilites and picnic, group & shelter areas are on the south side of the causeway.

NAME: A.W. Young Park
NOTES: Park Avenue Park (A.W. Young Park) is and inland park located between Canal 5 and Canal 6 on Indian River. There is marked access on Park Ave. E.

NAME: Vero Beach
NOTES: Vero Beach has limited parking at Riomar Dr and pedestrian access at Ladybug, Gayfeather, Flamevine Lanes.

NAME: Sexton Plaza
NOTES: Access to the beach is at the end of Beachland Blvd. E.  There is 2-hour parking in the plaza lot.

NAME: Humiston Beach Park
NOTES: Humiston Beach Park provides 500 feet of developed beach. It is reached by taking US 60 east to Ocean Drive South for about 0.5 miles to Dahlia Lane; access is marked.

NAME: Round Island Oceanfront Park
NOTES: Boating factilites are located directly across SR A1A.  There is a boat ramp, canoe launch and additional restrooms, picnic tables and parking.

NAME: Jack Island Preserve State Park
NOTES: Jack Island Preserve is part of Fort Pierce Inlet State Park.  There is a 1-mile trail (Marsh Rabbit Run Trail) across the island to the observation tower, as well as a 4.3-mile perimeter trail.

NAME: Pepper Beach Park
NOTES: Pepper Beach Park has basketball and tennis courts, a beach volleyball area, a baseball field, and a play area.

NAME: St. Lucie County Access
NOTES: There is pedestrian access at the ends of Flamingo Blvd, Sea Oats Rd, Moorings Lane and Shorewinds Dr.  There are no facilities and no parking.

NAME: Ft. Pierce Inlet State Park
NOTES: Fort Pierce Inlet State Park has beach access on the Atlantic, as well as on the Inlet side (swimming is restricted here). There is a multi-purpose trail through the park and a Coastal Hammock Nature Trail.

NAME: Jetty Park
NOTES: Restrooms are currently being constructed.

NAME: Surfside Park
NOTES: Surfside Park is 6,000 feet south of Fort Pierce Inlet; 2.8 acres of developed, urban beach park. Limited parking.  Restrooms are currently being constructed.

NAME: Jaycee Park
NOTES: Jaycee Park is across South Ocean Dr. (SR A1A) from Surfside Park; access west toward the Indian River. Vending machines available. Play area.

NAME: Coconut Drive Park
NOTES: Coconut Dr. Park has 81 feet of undeveloped beach at the south end of Surfside Dr. on Coconut Dr.  No alcohol.

NAME: Exchange Park
NOTES: Exchange Park: 1.5 undeveloped acres about 2.25 miles south of Fort Pierce Inlet; access off Blue Heron Blvd.

NAME: Frederick Douglas Memorial Park
NOTES: Frederick Douglas Memorial Park: 1,040 feet, this developed park is located 4 miles south of Fort Pierce Inlet on SR A1A.

NAME: Middle Cove Beach Access
NOTES: Middle Cove Beach Access: 110 feet of undeveloped beach, 5 miles south of Fort Pierce Inlet.

NAME: Blind Creek Beach
NOTES: Blind Creek Beach is currently closed due to hurricane damage.

NAME: Herman's Bay Access
NOTES: Herman's Bay Access is in the process of being relocated due to development.

NAME: Normandy Beach
NOTES: Normandy Beach Access: 110 feet of secluded, undeveloped beach, 11 miles south of Fort Pierce Inlet.

NAME: Jensen Beach Park
NOTES: Jensen Beach Park has 3,000 feet of developed beach. Access is at the intersection of SR 707A and SR A1A. Dune walkovers, bicycle facilities, a boardwalk, and a concession stand are available.

NAME: Bob Graham Beach
NOTES: Bob Graham Beach is located 3,500 feet south of Jensen Beach on SR A1A. It has 2,000 feet of undeveloped beach with dune crossovers.

NAME: Stuart Beach
NOTES: Stuart Beach/Martin Co. Park is 5 acres of developed oceanfront park on MacArthur Blvd. Off SR A1A. It has bicycle facilities, 150 parking spaces, a 250-foot boardwalk, and dune crossovers.
NOTES_2: On the property is the Elliot Museum, housing a collection of Americana dating as far back as 1750.

NAME: House of Refuge Beach
NOTES: House of Refuge Beach lies one mile south of Stuart Beach on Gilbert's Bar, Hutchinson Island. The oldest standing structure in Martin County, built in 1875, served as a rescue and refuge center for shipwrecked sailors.
NOTES_2: Current site of sea turtle research.  Pier located across Macarthur Blvd.

NAME: Bathtub Reef
NOTES: Bathtub Reef is 1,100 feet of undeveloped beach at the south end of Hutchinson Island, just north of St. Lucie inlet. An offshore reef forms a shallow "bathtub" where snorkeling is excellent.

NAME: St. Lucie Inlet State Recreation Area
NOTES: St. Lucie Inlet State Recreation Area has over 2.5 miles of remote beach on the north end of Jupiter Island just south of St. Lucie Inlet. Access to this area (under development) is by boat.

NAME: Hobe Sound National Wildlife Refuge
NOTES: Hobe Sound National Wildlife Refuge has 4 miles of ocean beach on the northern end of MacArthur Blvd. on Jupiter Island.

NAME: Hobe Sound
NOTES: Hobe Sound Beach lies approximately 2 miles north of bridge Road on Jupiter Island.

NAME: Blowing Rocks Preserve
NOTES: The Nature Conservancy's Blowing Rocks Preserve, near the southern Martin County border, has several trails available (both gulf & lagoon sides) as well as the Hawley Education Center, located across S Beach Rd.

NAME: Blowing Rocks Beach (Coral Cove Park)
NOTES: Coral Cove Park (Blowing Rocks Beach) is a developed beach with rock formations one mile south of Martin County on Jupiter Island. It has 600 feet of beachfront accessible via SR A1A. Lifeguards on weekends and holidays.

NAME: Jupiter Beach Park
NOTES: Jupiter Beach Park is a developed beach (1,700) feet with lifeguards. Access is off SR A1A on Beach Dr. just south of Jupiter Inlet on the ocean.

NAME: DuBois Park
NOTES: DuBois Park has 20 acres of developed beach with lifeguards; accessible via SR A1A on DuBois Rd. south of Jupiter Inlet.

NAME: Jupiter Island Park
NOTES: Jupiter Island Park in North Palm Beach County is surrounded by the Intracoastal Waterway. This rocky beach is reached via US 1, north of Indiantown Rd. (SR 706), south of Jupiter Inlet and SR A1A.

NAME: Carlin Park
NOTES: Carlin Park is a developed recreation area with 3,000 feet of rocky beach on the Atlantic Ocean with lifeguards. Access is on SR A1A, south of Indiantown Rd. (SR 706) in Jupiter.

NAME: Juno Beach Park
NOTES: Juno Beach Park lies one mile north of Juno Beach city limits on SR A1A. It has 3000 feet of undeveloped beach with lifeguards. Fishing pier.

NAME: Pegasus Park (Loggerhead Park)
NOTES: Loggerhead Park (Pegasus Park) has 900 feet of beachfront. It is located on SR A1A and US 1 about 1/8 of a mile north of Donal Ross Rd. north of Juno Beach.

NAME: Juno Beach
NOTES: Juno Beach has a small (2,600 feet), undeveloped oceanfront beach that is difficult to find as it is not marked (as of 1983). It lies about 3/4 mile south of Donald Ross Rd. on SR A1A. No alcohol allowed. Fishing pier available.

NAME: McArthur State Recreation Area
NOTES: John D. McArthur State Recreation Area (formerly Air Force Beach) is located on Singer Island between Lake Worth and the Atlantic Ocean. This is a new state park with plans for development of 8,000 feet of oceanfront beach in 1985.
NOTES_2: Access is off SR A1A, 2.5 miles north of Riviera Beach. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Howard Beach
NOTES: Howard Beach (Diamond Head) is 700 feet of undeveloped beach on SR A1A, directly north of the Hilton Inn on Singer Island.

NAME: Riviera Beach Municipal Park
NOTES: Riviera Beach Municipal Park has three marked access points off Blue Heron Blvd. In Riviera Beach east of I-95. This is a developed beach with lifeguards.

NAME: Palm Beach Shores Park
NOTES: Palm Beach Shores Park is a developed beach north of Lake Worth Inlet. It has 3,000 feet of beachfront with lifeguards.

NAME: Palm Beach Municipal Beach
NOTES: Palm Beach Municipal Beach has unlimited access to 6 miles of undeveloped beach with lifeguards. A large portion of the beach is bulkheaded. Parking is very limited. The beach runs about 3 miles both north and south of Royal Palm Way off SR A1A. No alcoh

NAME: Phipps Ocean Park
NOTES: Phipps Ocean Park has 1,300 feet of developed beach. Marked access is on Ocean Blvd., 2.5 miles south of Southern Blvd. Bridge. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Richard G. Kreusler Park
NOTES: Richard G. Kreusler Park has 450 feet of developed, rocky beach with lifeguards. Access is on SR A1A in Palm Beach, directly north of Lake Worth Public Beach.

NAME: Lake Worth Beach
NOTES: Lake Worth Beach, in Palm Beach, is accessible at Ocean Blvd (SR A1A) and Lake Ave. (SR 802). This is a developed beach (1,200 feet) with a pool and lifeguards. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Lantana Park
NOTES: Lantana Park lies between Lake Worth and the Atlantic Ocean one mile east of Lantana at the intersection of SR 12 and Ocean Blvd. (SR A1A). This is an undeveloped beach with lifeguards. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Manalapan Beach
NOTES: Manalapan Beach is an undeveloped beach about 1,350 feet south of Lantana Ave.

NAME: Boynton Inlet Park
NOTES: Boynton Inlet Park has access to 6000 feet of beach, in the town of Ocean Ridge, on SR A1A, directly south of the South Boynton Inlet and north of Island Dr.

NAME: Ocean Ridge Hammond Park
NOTES: Ocean Ridge Hammock Park lies north of Boynton Public Beach. It has 1,100 feet of undeveloped beach accessible from SR A1A, in Ocean Ridge.

NAME: Boynton Public Beach
NOTES: Boynton Public Beach is 2 blocks north of the I-95 exit on SR A1A in Ocean Ridge.

NAME: Gulf Stream County Park
NOTES: Gulf Stream County Park has 600 feet of developed beach on SR A1A, south of Briny Breezes mobile home community, north and east of the St. Andrews Club.

NAME: Delray Public Beach
NOTES: Delray Public Beach is accessible along the entire 7,000-foot length bordering the east side of Ocean Blvd. in Delray Beach. This is a developed beach with lifeguards. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: Atlantic Dunes Park
NOTES: Atlantic Dunes Park, on SR A1A approximately one mile south of Delray Public Beach, has 7 acreas of developed beach with lifeguards. No alcohol is allowed.

NAME: Spanish River Park
NOTES: Spanish River Park lies one mile east of Boca Raton. Access points are on Ocean Blvd. (SR A1A) just south of NE Spanish River Blvd. in Boca Raton. This developed beach covers 49 acres of the island from the Atlantic Ocean to the Intracoastal Waterway.
NOTES_2: It has over a half mile of beachfront with lifeguards. No alcohol is allowed.

NAME: Red Reef Park
NOTES: Red Reef Park, about one mile south of Spanish River Park on SR A1A, has access to 67 acres of developed beach with lifeguards. No alcohol is allowed.

NAME: South Beach Park
NOTES: South Beach Park is on SR A1A (Ocean Blvd.) at NE 4th St. The beach and ocean can be reached from three locations in the park. This is an undeveloped beach with lifeguards. No alcohol is allowed.

NAME: South Inlet Park
NOTES: South Inlet Park has 850 feet of developed beach with lifeguards on SR A1A, directly south of Boca Inlet.

NAME: Deerfield Beach
NOTES: Deerfield Beach is an undeveloped beach with 3,030 feet of beach frontage. Access is off SR A1A. North Beach: at NE 7th St., 4th Ct., and 2nd St. Central Beach: at Access Way, SE 1st St. through SE 4th St.
NOTES_2: South Beach: at SE 6th, 7th, 9th, and 10th streets.

NAME: Deerfield Island Park
NOTES: Deerfield Island Park is a destination island park for boaters. These 56 acres are accessible only by water.

NAME: Pompano Beach
NOTES: Pompano Beach has 3,000 feet of developed beach with lifeguards. Access is off North Ocean Blvd. (SR A1A) at NE 10th St, NE 7th St, NE 5th Ct., NE 5th St.; at 2nd St SE, 4th St SE, 6th St. SE, and 8th St. SE.
NOTES_2: A public parking lot is located between NE 5th St. and Atlantic Blvd. (SR 814). Fishing pier.

NAME: Lauderdale-by-the-Sea
NOTES: Lauderdale-by-the-Sea has a shoreline of about one mile accessible on Pine Ave., Washington Ave., El Prado, Commerical Rd. (SR 870), Datura Ave., Hibiscus Ave., Palm Ave., and Flamingo Dr. No alcohol allowed. Fishing pier.

NAME: St. Johns County Pier
NOTES: Located at the north end of St. Augustine Beach off A1A, just south of Pope Rd.

NAME: Surfside Park
NOTES: North Beach Access #29. Off-beach parking & vehicular access.

NAME: Gate Station Beach
NOTES: South Ponte Vedra Beach Access #28.

NOTES: Several trails located across Guana River Dam.

NAME: Mickler's Landing Beach
NOTES: Ponte Vedra Beach Access #15.

NAME: Ocean Front Park
NOTES: Guards may not be on duty. Play area.

NAME: Jacksonville Pier
NOTES:
Located between 4th & 5th Ave N.
Guard may not be on duty.

NAME: North Ocean Front Park
NOTES: Guards may not be on duty.

NAME: Little Talbot Island State Park - North Beach Pavilion Area
NOTES:
Beverage vending machine.
2.4-mile Island Hiking Trail starts at the Ranger Station & ends at the very north end of the beach.

NAME: Big Talbot Island State Park
NOTES:
Access to Nassau Sound.
3 short trails to the beach are available (Big Pine Trail, Blackrock Trail & the Shoreline Access Trail), as well as the more extensive Old Kings Highway Trail, just west of A1A.
NOTES_2: Boat ramp & full restroom facilities located just south of George Crady Bridge.

NAME: Scott Road Beach Access
NOTES: Vehicular access.

NAME: Fort Clinch State Park - Sound
NOTES:
Access to Cumberland Sound.
Willow Pond Nature Trail (25 & 45 minute loops). Bicycle trail runs through park.
Visitor's center & Ft Clinch Historic Site.
Beverage vending machines.
Play area.
No swimming due to dangerous currents.

NAME: St. Johns County South Beaches
NOTES:
Parking available at Access #167 (Spyglass).

NAME: Long Key State Park
NOTES: Long Key State Recreation Area has 1.5 miles of passive recreation and camping fronting the Atlantic Ocean. Abundant wading bird populations inhabit this area of mangrove lagoons and tropical hardwood hammocks on an ancient coral reef.

NAME: Sombrero Beach County Park
NOTES: Switlick County Park/Marathon Recreation Complex has 1,500 feet of beach located at the end of Sombrero Beach Road on Maraton Key.

NAME: Bahia-Honda State Park (Ocean Side) - Loggerhead Beach
NOTES: Bahia-Honda State Recreation Area has 1,548 feet on Bahia Honda Key. This skeleton of an ancient coral reef covered by beach, dunes, and mangroves is the state's southernmost recreation area.
NOTES_2: Tropical plants and rare species of birds flourish in the warm climate.

NAME: Little Duck Key County Park
NOTES: Little Duck Key County Park has 1,400 feet fronting the Atlantic Ocean on Little Duck Key.

NAME: Big Pine Key Park
NOTES: Big Pine Key Park is an undeveloped county park fronting Florida Bay on Big Pine Key.

NAME: George Smathers Beach
NOTES: George Smathers Beach has 3,945 feet of developed beach on South Roosevelt Blvd., Key West.

NAME: Clarence Higgs Memorial Beach
NOTES: Clarence Higgs Memorial Beach has 300 feet of developed Atlantic beach off Atlantic Blvd., Key West.

NAME: South Beach
NOTES: South Beach has 200 feet fronting Hawk Channel at the south end of Duval St., Key West.

NAME: Ft. Jefferson National Monument
NOTES: Fort Jefferson National Monument is an isolated, primitive beach on Garden Key, Dry Tortugas. Access by boat (docking permitted only at designated locations not to exceed 2 hours) or seaplane.

NOTES: Located just west of Parking Area #1.

NAME: Middle Cape
NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. The following are located off Monroe County's Gulf Coast.
NOTES_2: They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat. Major use is by overnight campers.

NAME: Anclote Key Preserve State Park
NOTES: Anclote Key, home to a newly restored 19th-Century Lighthouse, remains an undeveloped park with minimal facilities (primative camping, picnic pavilions & grills). It is located in the Gulf of Mexico, three miles off the Tarpon Springs mainland.
NOTES_2: The 3,000-foot beach is accessible only by boat.

NAME: Fred Howard County Park
NOTES: The Howard County Park beach is connected to the mainland by a mile-long causeway. Fishing is allowed only in designated areas. Trails, shelters and picnic & group areas are located on the mainland.
NOTES_2: Access is a half mile north of Keystone Rd (SR 582) on Florida Ave N in Tarpon Springs. No alcohol is allowed.

NAME: Sunset Beach at Tarpon Springs
NOTES: Sunset Beach is an undeveloped beach with a municipal pier located in Tarpon Springs at the end of Gulf Road (SR 582).

NAME: Honeymoon Island State Park North Beach
NOTES: Honeymoon Island State Park has over 10,000 feet of beachfront with dune walkovers and group facilities. Access is via SR 586 west over Dunedin Causeway. No alcohol is allowed.

NAME: Honeymoon Island State Park Dunedin Beach
NOTES: Dunedin Beach is an undeveloped beach on Honeymoon Island.  Access to Dunedin Beach was closed at the time of this survey.

NAME: Caladesi Island State Park
NOTES: Caladesi Island State Park may be reached only by boat. There is ferry service from the pier at Honeymoon Island State Park to the north in Dunedin. It has 2 miles of developed beach with group facilities. No alcohol is allowed.

NAME: Clearwater Beach Island North Beach
NOTES: Clearwater Beach Island lies between Clearwater Beach and the Gulf of Mexico and is connected to the Clearwater central business district by Memorial Causeway (SR 60).
NOTES_2: Pedestrian access to this beach is available at Eldorado Ave on Juniper St, Laurel St, Gardenia St, Bohemia Cir, Mango St and Bohmia Cir S.

NAME: Mandalay Park
NOTES: Mandalay Park has 500 feet of city-owned, developed beachfront.  Access is gulfside off Mandalay Ave. a half mile north of SR 60 (Memorial Causeway) on Clearwater Beach Island.  There is a metered parking lot between Kendall and Rockaway Streets.

NAME: Clearwater Beach Park
NOTES: Clearwater Beach Park is a developed beach (approximately a half mile long) with lifeguards, located on the south end of Clearwater Beach Island off Gulfview Blvd.
NOTES_2: There is metered street parking and parking lots available from First to Fifth Streets along S. Gulfview Blvd.  No alcohol is allowed.  Fishing pier and bicycle facilities.

NAME: Sand Key County Park
NOTES: Sand Key County Park has 2,100 feet of beachfront. Access on Clearwater Beach Island is south on SR 699 about 1.5 miles from Memorial Causeway (SR 60).  Vending machines selling beverages, snack and sunscreen available.

NAME: Belleair Shores Beach
NOTES: Belleair Shores Beach Access off N. Gulf Shore Blvd (SR 699) on 7th St., 13th St. and 19th St.  Local parking is unavailable.

NAME: Indian Rocks Beach
NOTES: Indian Rocks Beach has 3 miles of developed beach and is along N. Gulf Shore Blvd. (SR 699) from 27th Ave. to 2nd Ave..  Limited parking is available at 27th Ave., 22nd Ave., 8th Ave. and 4th Ave.  Pedestrian access is available at most streets inbetween
NOTES_2: There are showers at most access points and picnic tables and handicapped access ramps at some points.

NAME: Indian Shores Beach
NOTES: There is pedestrian access to Indian Shores Beach along SR 699 (Gulf Blvd.) from 199th to 197th Streets, at 193rd St., 190rd St. and 186th St.  There is no parking available.

NAME: Redington Shores Beach County Park
NOTES: Redington Shores County Park is on Gulf Blvd (SR 699) in Redington Shores at 182nd Avenue. It has about 50 feet of undeveloped beach. No alcohol allowed.

NAME: East Cape
NOTES: Everglades National Park has 1.4 million acres of marshy land covered with tall grasses that support a variety of birdlife, manatee, the Florida panther, and alligator. The following are located off Monroe County's Gulf Coast.
NOTES_2: They are remote, wilderness beaches accessible only by boat. Major use is by overnight campers.

NAME: Shell Key Preserve
NOTES: Shell Key Preserve, just north of Ft. DeSoto,  is a 1,755 acre preserve, which includes a 95 acre Bird Preservation Area. Access is allowed only on the north & south ends of the island. Camping allowed; no facilities.

NAME: Egmont Key State Park
NOTES: Historic Egmont Key, located at the mouth of Tampa Bay is home to the first lighthouse on Florida's west coast and to the ruins of Fort Dade. There are also numous trails to enjoy. No facilities.

NAME: Picnic Island Park
NOTES: Access by Picnic Island Blvd, off W Commerce St, just west of Macdill Air Force Base. Play areas. Large & small group areas.

NAME: Sand Spit Park
NOTES: Very limited street parking along 1st & G Streets.

NAME: Fort Island Gulf Beach

NAME: Hodges Park at Keaton Beach

NAME: Horseshoe Beach

NAME: Shired Island

NOTES_2: The Fishbone Creek Observation Tower provides lovely views over the marsh and the Dixie Mainline Road Guided Trail allows vehicular access through the refuge.
